## Context

The highest-risk seam is the API response shape contract. TypeScript types must be co-owned in `src/types/api.ts` and imported by both the API serialiser and client-side normaliser to prevent shape drift.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `src/types/api.ts` defines: `ProjectSummary`, `RunDetail`, `RunStageEntry`, `AgentConfig`, `LimitsSnapshot`, `CostSummary`
- [ ] `RunStageEntry.premiumRequests` typed as `number | null`
- [ ] Status typed as `'active' | 'awaiting_review' | 'blocked' | 'completed'` (confirmed by DISC-01-C1)
- [ ] Backend imports from shared types file -- no duplicate definitions
- [ ] Frontend store normaliser imports from same shared file

## Technical Notes

```typescript
type ProjectStatus = 'active' | 'awaiting_review' | 'blocked' | 'completed';
interface RunStageEntry {
  stage: string; agent: string; model: string; provider: string;
  durationMs: number; premiumRequests: number | null;
  changedFiles: string[]; summaryExcerpt: string;
}
```

- Cost calc: `(premiumRequests ?? 0) * 0.10` per stage
- `designTeam` and `buildTeam` pre-derived server-side -- frontend must not encode this logic
